<h3 id="strategies-for-surviving-the-search">Strategies for Surviving the Search</h3>

<p><strong>1. Set Sustainable Rhythms</strong></p>

<p>Don‚Äôt burn out applying to 50 jobs a day.</p>

<p><strong>Better approach:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>5-10 quality applications per week</li>
  <li>Customize each application</li>
  <li>Track where you‚Äôve applied</li>
  <li>Follow up appropriately</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>2. Keep Building While Searching</strong></p>

<p>Continue learning and building projects:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Maintains your skills</li>
  <li>Gives you something positive to focus on</li>
  <li>Creates portfolio pieces</li>
  <li>Shows dedication on your GitHub</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>3. Practice Interview Skills</strong></p>

<p>Interview skills are separate from coding skills.</p>

<p><strong>Practice:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Mock interviews with friends or community members</li>
  <li>LeetCode/HackerRank (if relevant to your target roles)</li>
  <li>Explaining your projects out loud</li>
  <li>Answering behavioral questions</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>4. Lean on Your Community</strong></p>

<p>This is when community matters most:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Share frustrations (it helps to vent)</li>
  <li>Get resume/portfolio reviews</li>
  <li>Practice interviews together</li>
  <li>Celebrate small wins</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>5. Take Care of Your Mental Health</strong></p>

<p>Job searching is emotionally draining.</p>

